          <h3>Do couples therapy apps really work?</h3>
          <p>Yes, many couples find therapy and relationship apps effective for improving communication, rebuilding trust, and increasing intimacy. They work best when both partners are committed to participating consistently. However, apps are generally best for mild to moderate relationship issues or as a supplement to traditional therapy, rather than a replacement for professional help in severe crisis situations.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-card">
          <h3>Are couples therapy apps covered by insurance?</h3>
          <p>Most self-guided relationship apps (like Paired, Lasting, or Love Nudge) are not covered by health insurance. However, apps that connect you directly with licensed therapists for live sessions (like ReGain or Ours) might be partially covered depending on your specific insurance plan and out-of-network benefits. Always check directly with your provider.</p>
